  "prompt": "My sibling lives with me and my husband rent-free. What are reasonable expectations from her in terms of household chores?",
  "response": "This is a nuanced situation that depends on several factors:\n\n1. Age and circumstances\n- Is she a student? \n- Is she working?\n- Is she temporarily between jobs?\n\n2. Potential contribution types\n- Regular chores (cleaning, dishes, laundry)\n- Occasional deep cleaning\n- Yard work\n- Meal preparation\n- Pet/child care\n- Running errands\n\n3. Communication recommendations\n- Have a clear, non-confrontational discussion\n- Agree on specific expectations\n- Create a chore schedule/division of labor\n- Be realistic about workload\n- Offer flexibility\n\n4. Typical fair expectations\n- Daily/weekly cleaning common areas\n- Cleaning own room/bathroom\n- Helping with dishes\n- Occasional grocery shopping\n- Maintaining shared spaces\n- Assisting with basic household maintenance\n\n5. Additional considerations\n- Consider her current life situation\n- Be supportive but maintain boundaries\n- Periodically review and adjust expectations\n- Ensure expectations are mutual and respectful\n\nThe key is open communication and creating a system that feels fair to everyone involved.\n\nWould you like to discuss specific details about your situation?",
